Governor of Sokoto State, Alhaji Aminu Tambuwal, has condoled with the family of former President Shehu Shagari, the people of Sokoto State and Nigeria over the death of the elder statesman, describing it as a great loss. In a statement by Director General, Media and Public Affairs, Abubakar Shekara, Tanbuwal noted that Shagari was a national and international statesman who made unparalleled contribution to the development of education, as a teacher at the basic level and president of Nigeria.  Shagari: Nigeria, Africa lost a statesman â€“ IBB ACF mourns Shagari Saraki, Dogara, Mark mourn Shagari